article.headline: SMU 77, San Jose State 69
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Bryan Hopkins scored 27 points to lead Southern Methodist to a 77-69 Western Athletic Conference victory Saturday over San Jose State. Hopkins made eight of 14 shots and eight of 10 from the foul line to lead the Mustangs (8-6 overall, 3-3 WAC). Three other SMU players scored in double figures -- Patrick Simpson with 17, Eric Castro with 14 and Devon Pearson with 13. Marquin Chandler led San Jose State (4-10, 1-4) with 19 points, while Donta Watson added 14 and Alex Elam 13. Chandler led all rebounders with 10, while Pearson had nine for the Mustangs. San Jose State led 19-18 with 8:50 remaining in the first half, but SMU scored 10 straight points and 18 of the next 20 to lead 36-21 with 2:12 left. Simpson scored seven points and Hopkins six to lead the charge. The Mustangs led 40-25 at halftime. Eight straight second-half points by Hopkins lifted SMU to a 58-42 advantage with 11:53 remaining in the game. San Jose State fought back to trail by just seven at 72-65 with 39 seconds left, but the Mustangs held on for the victory. SMU made 51 percent of its shots from the field, while San Jose State made just 39 percent.
